CatDescriptText: The certificate on the back wall reads "Richard Nixon, President of the United States of America, to all who shall see this presents greeting....Brady Keys, of California, Member of the Advisory Council for Minority Enterprise for a term of two years..."Brady Keys was a Pittsburgh Steeler football player and owner of Urban Talent Development, and Richard Barber was president of Urban Talent Development.
TitMainTitle: Two men, Richard Barber, and Brady Keys, holding book "Urban Talent Development, Inc." in office with certificate on wall from Richard Nixon to Brady Keys, Jr.
